      <guid>https://terourou.org/team/tom/</guid>
      <description>Tom completed his PhD in Statistics at the University of Auckland in 2020, which explored ways of improving the reliability of real-time bus arrival time prediction in Auckland by accounting for real-time traffic conditions. Since 2015, he have been the lead developer of iNZight, a free, easy-to-use data analysis and visualisation tool for statistics learners. Both the research and iNZight combine his two passions: computing and making tools to help others make sense of the world.</description>
